│ transforms a `cttz` intrinsic call with `is_zero_poison=false` to           │
│ `is_zero_poison=true` when used as a shift amount, without ensuring the     │
│ input is non-zero. This changes defined behavior (where `cttz(0, false)`    │
│ returns 32 for i32) to undefined behavior (where `cttz(0, true)` returns    │
│ poison).                                                                    │
│                                                                             │
│ The fix is to modify the transformation in                                  │
│ `/llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCa │
│ lls.cpp` in the `foldCttzCtlz` function to only apply when the input is     │
│ known to be non-zero, using the `isKnownNonZero` function.                  │
